<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="K" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Kingly1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Kingly,</orth> adj. 1) royal, of royal rank, pertaining to a king: <cit><quote>k. poor flout,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.269" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 269</bibl></cit> (poor mockery of a king). <cit><quote>thy k. hand,</quote> <bibl n="shak. aww 2.1.196" default="NO" valid="yes">All's II, 1, 196</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. per 4.1.55" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. IV, 1, 55</bibl>. <cit><quote>my k. guest,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 3.2.167" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. III, 2, 167</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a k. eye,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 5.1.47" default="NO" valid="yes">John V, 1, 47</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. ham 4.7.45" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. IV, 7, 45</bibl>. <cit><quote>sway,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 4.206" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 IV, 206</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>thy k. doom,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 5.6.23" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 6, 23</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the k. couch,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 3.1.16" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B III, 1, 16</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>I give thee k. thanks,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.3.163" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A V, 3, 163</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>my k. throne,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 3h6 1.1.124" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C I, 1, 124</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>by your k. leave,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.2.63" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 63</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>k. sepulchres,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 3h6 5.2.20" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 20</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the k. government,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 3.7.132" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 7, 132</bibl></cit>. <emph>title,</emph> 239 (Ff <emph>royal</emph>). <cit><quote>glory,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 4.4.371" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 371</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>dignity,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h8 2.4.227" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 II, 4, 227</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>his k. ears,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 1.3.219" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. I, 3, 219</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>crown,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jc 3.2.101" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. III, 2, 101</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>seal,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 3.13.125" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. III, 13, 125</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>patient,</quote> <bibl n="shak. per 5.1.71" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. V, 1, 71</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) like a king, becoming a king: <cit><quote>flat treason 'gainst the k. state of youth,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 4.3.293" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL IV, 3, 293</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a king, woe's slave, shall k. woe obey,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 3.2.210" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 III, 2, 210</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>her almost k. dukedoms,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 1.2.227" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 I, 2, 227</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>more k. in my thoughts,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 5.1.29" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B V, 1, 29</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the k. lion,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 3h6 5.7.11" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C V, 7, 11</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the k. crowned head,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cor 1.1.119" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. I, 1, 119</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>